<br>
The problem is that you're wedged between the northeast patrol route, the middle patrol route, and Maestro's house o' roamers. Any direction you move to will give you a train of between 6 and 20something mobs.<br>
<br>
Also, you'd have almost zero room to fight as agro along the Maestro wall house will cause the mobs inside to aggro to you. They will then path to the back, aggroing Maestro and the 20 things that live there, and also bleed agro through the wall grabbing the northeast route and a house of revs or two.<br>
<br>
Now, this might sound insane but.. you could just walk up the steps and then as soon as you get off the staircase, there's a couple of drakes and some dead ends. If you get lucky and don't take a launching from a drake, you could back into a dead end and fight there, then just bring mobs up to the camp, having your feign spot on the steps just outside the camp.  It'd take some coordination from all involved, but it'd work if you knew the second floor had the miniboss you needed to remove. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=durokh>DurokH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/14/03 9:37:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3649.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the replies.  We think we're gonna give it a try with two decent groups.  I'll report back on what happens.<br>
